\title{Recovering a propositional theory from a class of models}
\import{macros}

\p{We can retrieve (the [syntactic category](math-003A) of) a [propositional theory](math-0039) #{\mathcal{B}} from its [class of models](math-003B) #{{\rm Mod}_\mathcal{B}} by considering the class of models [as a Stone space](math-003D):
}

##{\mathcal{B} \cong \Hom_{\mathbf{Stone}}({\rm Mod}_\mathcal{B}, 2)}

\p{Where #{2} is the two-element [Stone space](math-002P).}